714137f-a.title: Manhattan: 63rd Street (East) - Lexington Avenue
714137f-a.text:
152 to 162 East 63rd Street, south side, between Lexington and Third
Aves., showing the home of Judge Samuel Seabury at No. 154 (double-front,
balcony thereon).
January 2, 1938.
George D. Chinn.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

721041f-a.title: Manhattan: Lexington Avenue - 63rd Street (East)
721041f-a.text:
Lexington Avenue, at the S. E. corner of East 63ro
Street, showing at this location the Temple Rodelph Sholem
(Followers of Peace). This structure was formerly the
Beth-El Synagogue and erected in 1873. To the left is a
view sastward to Third Avenue on the south side of 63rd St.
April, 1926
MAY BE REPRODUCED
